rComments: Professor Nicholas Hoell can always make math interesting for me, and he is hilarious! The midterms for MAT224 are, in my opinion, too much of a time crunch but the final was great. He sparked my interest in mathematics.

If you just want to do well on tests without putting much effort into learning the material or if you want to want to pass his class without putting much effort into understanding the topics, you won't like him. However, if you want to learn deeply about the material and fully understand concepts, he's your guy. He's extremely knowledgeable btw.

Very good professor but very hard course... Yes it has "data science" in the course's name but it is a Specialist-level MATH course! Get used to abstract notions like inner product associated in normed vector space, unit ball in higher dimensions, etc. and get used to rigorous proofs. I dropped because of time conflict though.
Easyyy Right? Linear algebra is simple but not easy. One of the best professors encountered in my life.
Nicholas is the best!! Enthusiastic and skilled lecturer.
Best professor in UofT. Full stop.
The lecture note he makes is really clear and helpful.
Made you understand the material but he makes hard tests. Be sure to study up solutions for previous tests.

amazing prof who made 223 a great learning experience, his humour makes the class rlly fun and he is very passionate about teaching math. Always stays way overtime for his office hours to make sure the students understand the material. Coolest prof out there
BEST PROF EVAAAAAAA

Honestly one of the best profs I've had at U of T so far. The material is abstract and hard to learn, but his passion made the lectures interesting, I would always look forward to going to his classes. His tests are not easy but fair, even though my grade was average, I still enjoyed the class a lot, hope to get him as my prof again in the future.

His lectures are for the most part, satisfactory for delivering the material. However, he does seem to go on tangents and spend entire classes on a single not-particularly useful proof. He comes off as incredibly arrogant and condescending at times. But, he said he wouldn't curve but I'm pretty sure he did in the end.

I wish I didn't have to take MAT223 for program requirement since the sole guide and friend in the course is your textbook. Hoell's teaching style is not for everybody, so I suggest to audit first before enroling in his course.

rComments: Great sense of humour.

He always says "easy right?" but don't be fooled by it. The tests are not easy and require the deep understanding of materials. He likes LU factorization but never show up in the tests. The final exam is fair but long.

Despite his habit of saying stuff are easy, I find him to be a great professor. He delivered concepts really well. This class required a lot of time put in practicing though. Amazing prof with an amazing sense of humor. His lectures are fairly rapid-pace but he is extremely passionate and does not skip a beat when it comes to explaining where everything comes from. Nothing gets generated out of thin air in his class.

His lectures are always jammed with lots of notes, lots of proofs and lots of theorems. Having good understandings of ALL the theorems and proofs are the essence and the most important thing in this course. Do practice questions! They help you to understand the theorems better!
